This place had such mixed reviews, and being that I   Love Middle Eastern food I had to try it for myself.  Went around dinner time after shopping nearby. I ordered the Arab Chix roll that everyone has photos of. They were nice enough to let me sub the Cole slaw. They bring the food to you but seem to forget napkins.  I ate outside, as the lighting inside is yucky. Fries are crisp as everyone says and seasoned with some addictive powder that seems to have sugar in it. Chix is ok, moist with a lemon-grassy flavor, dark meat so a bit in the oily side for me. Labneh (aka white sauce) is super salty and they didn’t have many non-soda options, so I was parched. My tabbouleh was fresh but the oil they used seems rancid, so I didn’t finish it. The spicy sauce was probably the best thing I had... I was nervous this would make sick, it was mainly heavy and I didn’t feel bad until the next day. This is basically a greasy shawarma joint, not really home cooking... *sorry about the bad photo- I have to delete some stuff bc my camera is slow

We just found a new favorite place to eat ❤. Delicious food and amazing customer service. We first tried the food when we actually were just driving  and thought to just try it. The guy there told us to try the arabic shawarma .. which we fell in love with and ordered another one. After eating in the restraunt a few times we thought of ordering it for delivery. 1st time we got the delivery it was a dissapointment food was very cold and dry. We called the manager and he was so friendly and apologized and ask us if we wanted a replacement food or full refund. I told him we will try ordering one more time in a few days. So he said whenever we order it would be free of charge.  Ok so we ordered the same food today with an extra drink. The food was fresh, tasty and flavorful. Plus they gave us free complimentry dessert(which was delicious too). And they did not charge us forthe extra drink.  I would highly recommend everyone to give this place a shot. And i have already shared this with all my family and friends.
